tags.description: The Leonora Curtin Wetland Preserve is a 35-acre nature preserve located on Los Pinos road south of Santa Fe. This rare natural cienega, or “marsh” in Spanish, hosts a bountiful diversity of plants and wildlife. Open June-October only.
